Interface IExtractedValue<T extends java.io.Serializable>


  • public interface IExtractedValue<T extends java.io.Serializable>
    Describes a value extracted by an IGlobalExtractionPhase.

    • Method Detail

      • getUniformPath

        java.lang.String getUniformPath()
        Returns the uniform path for this value.

      • getValue

        java.lang.String getValue()
        Returns the actual value. This is also used as key in the inverted index.

      • getAdditionalInformation

        T getAdditionalInformation()
        Returns additional information that should be stored. This is information that later needs to be available to the check, but is not part of the value. Examples are token positions of the values.
